The '''Entuurans''' were a [[Human/Legends|Human]] culture that shared its name with [[Entuur]], a celestial body<ref name="AIR" /> in the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim's]] [[Urce sector/Legends|Urce sector]],<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Entuur system/Legends|Entuur system]]</ref> as well as the procedures known as [[Entuuran resilience tests]]. The Entuurans valued pain and suffering. The [[Gender/Legends|male]] Human [[Mox Slosin]], who was [[Reproduction/Legends|born]] sometime between five and six [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]] prior to<ref name="AIR" /> [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Dates">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', which establishes that [[Mox Slosin]] already served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] approximately two and a half [[Standard year/Legends|years]] prior to its setting, represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one year before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> was an Entuuran from Entuur who had entered service to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] by<ref name="AIR" /> [[1 BBY/Legends|1 BBY]]<ref name="Dates" /> and had become an Imperial [[High Inquisitor]]<ref name="AIR" /> by 2 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]].<ref name="Dates" /> Slosin's sadistic tendencies potentially originated with his Entuuran upbringing.<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Entuurans were mentioned in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''. In the book, the Entuuran Mox Slosin was illustrated by [[Matt Busch]].<ref name="AIR" />

